


  
  
   NG - lifecycle
   --------------
   
   
   ref : https://www.toptal.com/angular-js/angular-js-demystifying-directives
   ref : https://github.com/Pasvaz/bindonce
   
   
   
   
   NG - directive life-cycle:-
   
   
     a. compilation-phase
     
     b. controller and pre-link phase
     
     c. post-link - phase
     
        will register 'watchers' ( listeners ) on every DOM element where data-binding required  
        
       
        watchers read/write model data on DOM elements when model is dirty on either side.
        
        
        all watchers are executed by 'digest-loop' 
        
        
       -------------------------------------------- 
       
       
     
   
   